tip.text: Mac and Wild is a perfect place if you love whiskys. The bar staff are friendly & happy to advise you on which whisky to try. For non-whisky lovers, try the Bloody Mary.
Tried out their new alto pizza. Looks better then it tastes- very doughy taste. May need to be cooked longer. shame as I had high hopes
Queued for ages &then squashed on a small table with other guests. The idli starter is seriously tasty. I didn't like the egg hopper, which was ruined by an overly sweet vegetarian kari. No desserts
Had a lovely vegetarian Christmas dinner. Such a beautifully decorated venue with lots of vegetarian options.
The vegetarian dim sum platter was excellent followed by the spicy tofu dish. The main was really good. I can't wait to go back. Lastly I loved the Rice Krispie chocolate dessert.

I missed the sign stating the cost of the ingredients, so ended up paying £11 for a vegetarian pizza, Plus £3 for a drink. this worked out an expensive experience. At that price, I've had better pizza
Lots of vegetarian options here. Highly recommend the chips&dip, grilled cauliflower,avocado sushi, the miso aubergine & the portobello mushroom with the buns. Really good food. Very cool concept.
Luxurious setting & a band plays @night. I ordered the vegetarian: spring rolls, veg dim sum, paneer &aubergine claypot. Besides from the claypot, dishes were average. The chocolate soufflé was wow
a fun place to go with a group. The place is impressive,can't wait to go back. Only gripe is the bar staff are rude. I Gave up waiting for a drink. if vegetarian avoid bab's vegetarian paneer kebab

Loved the vegetarian starters (burrata, ratatouille & the grilled broccoli is a must). The veg mains were plain & sub standard, especially the tomato pasta.The chocolate mousse dessert though... wow!!
Lots of vegetarian options available. Enjoyed the makhani dal and the chilli tofu. Don't get the garlic paneer & veg. The service was really good.

Tried the vegetarian dishes on the£29 tasting menu. The veg dimsum was seriously good. There was only one choice as a main which was a bean curd dish. Although it looked fantastic, I wasn't impressed.
Surprised at how many options available for vegetarians. They have a vegan menu not on the website. Loved the avocado sushi, aubergine miso & the chocolate dessert. Great atmosphere
Great vegetarian choices for breakfast/brunch. Healthy & tasty. Busy so make sure you book.
Vegan fro-yo, which is open until late. The store itself is very funky. As far as the taste of the yogurt, I prefer Snog's frozen yogurt but worth checking out.
Enjoyed a cooking demonstration here. Great concept
This is a stunning club, with 4 rooms to cater for all music types. This is a must when you go to Valencia.

contact.facebookName: Ciutat de les Arts i les Ciències - Ciudad de las Artes y las Ciencias

formattedAddress: Av. Professor López Piñero, 5 (Ciudad de las Artes y las Ciencias)
location.crossStreet: Ciudad de las Artes y las Ciencias

tip.text: Wow wow!! This place is a must- so much fun & the singing & dancing is phenomenal. It isn't cheap but well worth it. Not many vegetarian dishes available but don't let that stop you.

formattedAddress: Puerto Deportivo Marina ibiza (Puerto Marina Ibiza)

tip.text: Amante is a must! The food is good & the location & decor is breathtaking. There are good vegetarian options, I went for the tiered vegetables (lasagne) 👍🏽. The food is so fresh. Highly recommend

formattedAddress: C. Fuera, s/n (Cala Sol d'en Serra)

tip.text: The rooms are huge & pool is stunning. on the weekend we were kept awake with the noise from the club. Water & wifi are both not complimentary. Cost of food, water, alcohol is super expensive

formattedAddress: 3131 Las Vegas Blvd S (at Sands Ave)

tip.text: The views here are incredible. Worth checking out & follow with a gelato!!
Came here for pesto making. Great experience & lovely staff who make you feel super welcome. Pesto is delicious. Try the focaccia with cheese
I went for the vegetarian hot dog from the brunch menu. It was ok, very simple. I wasn't a fan of the mac & cheese as the cheese was overwhelming. The place was buzzing due to the bottomless presecco
Went on the bikes&hikes tour & thoroughly enjoyed it. Great views of the city
Service is top notch. I went for the savoury crepe but personally I prefer sweet. Would def go back to try. Best place for breakfast but expect Long queues.
Hands down this place has amazing food. Really popular & can see why. Order the broccolini & the spicy pizza with burrata. Service is great too. Just a shame they don't have wifi.
I tried the Californian vegetarian sandwich but on sour dough. Really tasty. So good that I went back & ordered a sour dough waffle. Again it couldn't be faulted. This is a must-visit in San Fran
No where fancy but great if you want a cheap & quick bite to it. Famous for its cragels. I went for a bagel with cream cheese. Can't go wrong here.

formattedAddress: 724 Bush St (btwn Powell St & Mason St)

tip.text: This is such a cool place, great vibe & stunning decor. Food is amazing with lots of vegan / vegetarian choices. Also, prices are reasonable considering in west Hollywood.

formattedAddress: 8905 Melrose Ave (at N La Peer Dr)

tip.text: Wow I love this place. The venue was so cool & the staff are super friendly. Highly recommend here.
The vegetarian option is only mushroom & polenta. I wasn't impressed & barely ate it. Shame as ambience & rustic decor are spot on.
Stunning decor &excellent service. Food was tasty, mix of Italian/Japanese. menu incl vegetarian options, pasta/risotto (carb overload). Chocolate cake dessert was ok not fan of smoked tea ice cream.
disappointed with the vegetarian food here. I tried all 3 options. The mushroom dish on sourdough was bland, edamame pancakes were salty. I did enjoy sake tiramisu for dessert. Go for drink only

Had the vegetarian avocado eggs Benedict. Really recommend. Spicy & healthy! Also loved Mac & cheese. For dessert, we ordered the blueberry pancakes, which were disappointing. Just not 'fluffy' enough
Cool place for cocktails around Marble Arch. Make sure you book as it gets super busy. The staff are friendly & great selection of cocktails. Loved the decor
Dinings didn't live up to the hype.Small restaurant with no Japanese identity to the decor. The vegetarian dishes were OK relative to the price you pay. All greatly presented but won't go back
Lots of vegetarian options, just ask for the veg menu. Fresh guacamole is seriously good as is the mexican brownie- best I've ever tasted. Personally the other dishes aren't as tasty as wahaca.

formattedAddress: 10 Upper St Martins Ln (at Shelton St)

tip.text: The vegan eggs Benedict is yum. A Funky cafe & Reasonably priced. Friendly staff. A real gem
Lovely hotel. 3 pools to choose from... Bliss
Great veggie breakfast. Nice vibe & hot chocolate was yum. It is expensive though
Pizza is really tasty. Don't order the veg risotto. Great atmosphere, will def go back
Great veg selection with teriyaki options & excellent whisky selection. Food portions are huge so don't over order. Unfortunately The restaurant lacks atmosphere.
The veggie taco is tasty and well priced
For vegetarians I like the truffle and cauliflower & the carrot starter. The risotto wasn't great for mains but there was nothing else to choose from. The chocolate tarte is so good & virgin mojitos
Nice views but the place has no atmosphere. I prefer Madison's. Also, you have to reserve an area to get in.
I love the veg doc tacos here and only £4.50! Spicy and delicious
